2022, year 25 into my 26th. 
I had a lot of first this year, along with that so much change I could barely hang on or keep up at times. Lots of pain, but with that came massive growth. This year felt messy, and I had to learn how to stop resisting and just be, feel and heal my way forward… because of that I am ending my year very present, very grounded, and happy with where I am at. Truly. For a lot of the year I just felt out of my body. There were times I felt I spread myself too thin and other times I said bring it on! It was in my deepest of pain this year that I understood who I have been, who I wanna be and who I am. I found myself truly surrendering to life.. putting my hands up and riding the rollercoaster that life is. I’ve had what feels like  insane perspective changes what I “can” tolerate but what I also don’t have to. How to just sit my ass down somewhere when I just didnt feel like carrying it on some days. Understanding that no one owes me anything but more so that I dont owe anyone anything either. That it’s all my choice. My mind. My feelings. My journey and it’s just for me. That I am capable of hard things and the only thing that can truly stand in my way is myself. I’ve learn how to eat sh*t and make mistakes but despite a hard fall getting back up and trying again. That all that matters is your best no matter how it looks. To validate myself and be my own biggest supporter and hold so closely to my heart the ones outside of myself that cheer me on too. How to be a better friend, daughter, sister, student and teacher. 

If you have been rockin’ with me this far, I just wanna say thank you so much. I truly value you. Thank you to my teachers and mentors and friends that lifted me up this year, and spoke life into me! 

For 2023, I have every intention on being the most kind to myself and seeing more dreams, goals and opportunities unfold before my very eyes. I’m aware of the value I hold and it’s because of overcoming tough battles and all of the people who were waiting for me at the end of the tunnel. Im going into this year holding hands with my people. Y’all are top tier and I love you. 💖

LA, I’ll see you in the New Year! 🤘🏽😝

Story Time..

I find this to be quite fascinating.
When I was 3 years old I got very sick. I don’t remember much but from what I am told.. I went from wrestling with my older brothers to being deathly sick in a matter of minutes. I ended up being in the ICU for 10 days. Every day I was presenting a new symptom. One day I had spots all over me and they thought it was just chicken pox, to then going as far as no longer being able to stand or walk the next. They thought they had found what was wrong with me and were going to perform surgery on my spine but I ended up showing another symptom so that didn’t happen. The doctors couldn’t figure out what was wrong with me and my entire family was very scared because I was extremely sick. 
Apparently there had been one doctor who was more eager to figure out what was wrong. He knew another doctor who he then brought in to see me. I had been very irritable and throwing fits at every doctor.. but apparently when this particular man walked in, I had become very calm.. so much that I ended up crawling into this man’s lap. This doctor ended up being the one to diagnose me with HSP (Henoch - Scholein purpura). Which is a rare virus that causes blood vessels in the skin, intestines, kidneys and joints to leak. From there they were not able to cure the virus itself, but they were able to treat the symptoms and alleviate my pain while my body took care of the virus itself. 

The only thing I remember from that time was the feeling of being deeply Ill / weak and a moment when doctors brought me a tub of Barbie’s to play with when I was in the hospital room. 

Anywho, I find it interesting how intuitive I already was at 3 years old but I also find it interesting that I was too young to remember yet was such a crazy experience in my own life. 

Children, are so special. Hugging my 3 year old self. ♥️

Clearly I’ve been fighting demons since I came into the world. 😂

Thoughts 💭 
- Get up and do all of the things / tasks that you would want to do if you had all of the free time in the world.. & not only start them, complete them. 

- You deserve to gift yourself things without feeling guilty, you work hard. 

- You are enough just as you are, naturally. 

- As women our bodies are always changing and going through phases, allow these phases to work for you and not against you. Listen to your body. 

- Any movement, is good movement.

- Gods time, not mine. 

- If it doesn’t feel good, it doesn’t feel good. Listen to that. 

- It’s ok to change direction, pace, and pause for a moment. 

- Just breathe.

- Surround yourself with the best people, but be aware that wolves can also come in sheep’s clothing. 

I love you all… I hope you’ve all done something positive and refreshing for yourself and your head space this weekend. I know I most certainly decided to indulge in myself, I dont do this enough..

I love being in the studio training so much, for the simple fact that it was something I didnt have or really know of growing up and now, I live in a place where it’s normal and the place where everyone comes to pursue their wildest and shiniest of dreams. 2023 was a year where I really felt myself outgrowing people, places, relationships, environments and some of my own habits and ways of thinking… & although that doesn’t always feel good, I care to grow.. and if these are the experiences I need to have in order to grow then so be it. It was a whirlwind of everything! All of the good, bad, highs, lows. 

But with growing pains, come feelings of having to redefine my “Why”… WHY am I doing this? WHY am I spending time here or there? WHY is this good or bad for me? WHY am I placing my energy in that thing or the person? WHY? 

I’ve also come to know the fact that you don’t have to be growing in ways where you have all of the bells and whistles to try to showcase or prove to others that you are doing things…. Sometimes real growth is quiet. It’s what’s happening inside you and sometimes people don’t catch onto that until much later. 

Then comes in the WHO? WHO am I surrounded by? WHO pours into me the same way I pour Into them? WHO supports me? (however that looks). WHO is rooting for me? WHO can I really call and depend on when life gets ugly? 

I’ve come to a place (still feels uncomfortable) where I care about how my life feels for me personally and not how it looks to other people or how other people think I should be living, moving, or operating or where others may think you should be. 

This year ive really learned to say the word NO. I’ve learned that I am allowed to rest and turn things down because I simply need to rest. I have truly learned that NOTHING is more important than the health of my mind, my heart and my spirit and if I have to turn everything off, I can. 
BOUNDARIES. 

2023 has been a year of putting my foot down. Standing up for myself and not feeling bad about it. 

In 2024 all I care about is moving with pure intentions and being and staying as authentic and true to myself as possible. 

Remembering what MY dreams are and have always been. Remembering and coming back to what sets ME on fire. What sets ME apart. What makes ME worth it. Standing in that and allowing all of my desires come to me as I remain in my power. 

2024… passionately rooted. 🌳
💚Grateful.

Moment of truth… 

This is my body after 2 1/2 weeks, of zero working out, enjoying holiday rest + food, then dialing back in on nutrition, dance, stretch, & recovery. 

I haven’t started my workout regimen back up yet. WHY? Well, all of the work I put in last year physically I was not recovering equally / enough. Because of that my body by end of last year going into this new year was WRECKED. I  knew I have absolutely needed to start back up slowly and properly so that I do not hurt myself and set new rest & recovery goals. My body both looks and feels way better now after fully resting, than it did last year when I was moving a TON and not recovering nearly enough. Rest is so so important. You are not a machine. You are a human, doing hard things and in order to do those hard things you need down time. 

My word of advice for you, as you start this New Year and you have those fitness goals is to BALANCE IN YOUR REST & RECOVERY.  No matter how busy you are. It is NECESSARY. 

As both a fitness professional and Dance Professional, this has come very very high on my priority list especially as I have taken on more work loads. Balance balance balance. It’s non negotiable. 

It’s all fun and games until you start getting to those late 20’s & closer to those 30’s. 😂 *Cant believe I’m saying that* 

Happy Tuesday my Loves, get after it and remember to set REASONABLE goals that will take you to LONGEVITY. 😘
